  "title": "AIRCON ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p>Job Responsibilities:</p><p></p><p>Design, install, and maintain air conditioning and HVAC systems for residential, commercial, and industrial projects.</p><p>Conduct load calculations and system evaluations to ensure efficient cooling performance.</p><p>Develop detailed technical drawings and specifications in collaboration with the design team.</p><p>Troubleshoot and diagnose issues in air conditioning systems and recommend solutions.</p><p>Ensure compliance with industry standards, safety regulations, and environmental guidelines.</p><p>Coordinate with clients, contractors, and project teams to ensure smooth project execution.</p><p>Prepare cost estimates, project reports, and technical documentation.</p><p>Perform site inspections and quality checks to verify system performance and installation accuracy.</p><p>Requirements:</p><p>Bachelor's degree or diploma in Mechanical Engineering, HVAC Engineering, or a related field.</p><p>Experience in air conditioning system design, installation, and maintenance.</p><p>Proficiency in HVAC design software and AutoCAD.</p><p>Strong knowledge of refrigeration principles, ventilation, and energy efficiency standards.</p><p>Excellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail.</p><p>Ability to work independently and collaborate with a team.</p><p></p>",
